# RELEASE — unbound-tumbleweed-config

Version:  v2.4
Date:     2026-04-30
Platform: openSUSE Tumbleweed
Unbound:  1.x

---

## What's in this release

### v2.4 — IPv6 block coverage + tracker expansion + Google admin UI whitelist
- `local.d/custom-blocks.conf` — every block now returns both `127.0.0.1` (A) and `::1` (AAAA)
  - Closes IPv6-first bypass — browsers querying AAAA only no longer leak around the block
- 21 new manually blocked domains covering major ad networks (doubleclick, googleadservices,
  adnxs, rubiconproject, taboola, outbrain, …) and analytics/measurement (google-analytics,
  googletagmanager, scorecardresearch, fullstory, optimizely, …)
- Google admin UI whitelist (3 `transparent` overrides) — Search Console, Analytics admin,
  Tag Manager admin work normally without re-enabling third-party trackers

---

### v2.3 — OISD Full + 127.0.0.1 everywhere
- `scripts/update-unbound-ads.sh` — new conversion script
  - Downloads OISD Full (~329,000 domains) and converts all `always_null` → `redirect + local-data A 127.0.0.1`
  - Eliminates `0.0.0.0` from all DNS block responses (CVE-2024 "0.0.0.0 Day" mitigation)
- `systemd-units/update-unbound-ads.service` — calls the conversion script; switched from Peter Lowe to OISD Full
- `local.d/custom-blocks.conf` — all entries now use `redirect + local-data A 127.0.0.1`; 10 new manual blocks added

---

### v2.2 — Manual blocklist + logrotate fix
- `local.d/custom-blocks.conf` — manual domain blocklist, independent of the pgl.yoyo.org list
  - Blocks `unityads.unity3d.com` (all subdomains) and `cookiebot.com` tracking CDN
- `logrotate.d/unbound` — fixed postrotate hook: `unbound-control log_reopen` instead of `systemctl reload`
- `unbound.conf` — updated include directives

---

### v2.1 — Complete production rewrite
- Full `unbound.conf` with detailed inline comments — every parameter documented
- DoH endpoint `doh.lan` via `local.d/doh-local.conf` — port 8053 (proxied by Caddy)
- Split DNS: local domains (bytel.fr, home.) forwarded to gateway without DNSSEC
- All other queries via QNAME minimization → Quad9 DoT (port 853, IPv4 + IPv6)

### Security & privacy
- DNSSEC full validation (`val-permissive-mode: no`) — bogus responses rejected
- `hide-identity`, `hide-version`, `use-caps-for-id` — anti-fingerprinting
- `deny-any: yes` — blocks DNS amplification
- `private-address` all RFC1918 ranges — full rebinding protection
- Rate limiting: 1000 req/s global, 200 req/s per IP

### Performance
- Message cache: 50 MB — RRset cache: 100 MB — Key cache: 16 MB
- 4 threads, `prefetch: yes`, `serve-expired: yes` (3600s stale)
- `edns-tcp-keepalive` — persistent TLS connections to Quad9

### Automated maintenance (systemd units)
- `update-unbound-ads` — weekly ad list update from OISD Full (329,000 domains, 127.0.0.1)
- `update-unbound-roots` — monthly root hints update from internic.net
- `unbound-anchor` — daily DNSSEC root trust anchor update

---

## Current configuration summary

| Parameter      | Value                          |
|----------------|--------------------------------|
| Listen port    | 53 (DNS) / 8053 (DoH)         |
| Upstream       | Quad9 9.9.9.9:853 DoT         |
| DNSSEC         | Full validation, strict mode   |
| Ad blocking    | OISD Full (~329,000 domains)   |
| Block response | 127.0.0.1 + ::1 (IPv4 + IPv6) |
| Threads        | 4                              |
| Cache total    | ~170 MB                        |
